  "prompt": "What does \"Quora \" mean?",
  "response": "Quora is a question-and-answer platform where users can ask questions and receive answers from the community. It was founded in 2009 by Adam D'Angelo and Charlie Cheever. The name \"Quora\" is derived from the word \"quorum,\" which refers to a group of people gathered together for a specific purpose, emphasizing the platform's goal of gathering knowledgeable individuals to share their insights and expertise on various topics. Users can follow specific topics, answer questions, and upvote responses, creating a collaborative environment for knowledge sharing.",
